== Date? ==

According to the [[Sicilian Wars]] article, there was a siege of Syracuse in 397 BC, but there is no mention of any battle in 387 BC. Is the date wrong?--[[User:SkiDragon|SkiDragon]] ([[User talk:SkiDragon|talk]]) 05:00, 20 May 2008 (UTC)
:I think you're right. There's also a mention of this siege on the [[397 BC]] page, but none on the [[387 BC]] page. It should probably be moved. [[User:Ems24|Ems24]] ([[User talk:Ems24|talk]]) 19:38, 4 March 2010 (UTC)
:Okay, I've moved it. If anyone has any objections, feel free to change it back. I'm not an expert on this subject. [[User:Ems24|Ems24]] ([[User talk:Ems24|talk]]) 19:48, 4 March 2010 (UTC)

== Title ==

It seems to me that title should be changed to "Siege of Syracuse (397 BC)", as the article almost exclusively refers to the event as a siege and not a battle. [[User:Ems24|Ems24]] ([[User talk:Ems24|talk]]) 19:41, 4 March 2010 (UTC)
